\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 88. S. spergulifolia} (Willd.) Bieb., {\i Fl. Taur.-Cauc.}{\b  3:} 305 (1820) ({\i Cucubalus spergulifolius} Willd.,{\i  S. armeniaca }Rohrb., {\i S. supina} Bieb.). Perennial with branched, woody stock. Stems numerous, 15-40 cm, procumbent or ascending to erect, scabrid-puberulent, somewhat glandular above. Leaves 15-40 × (0·5-)1-4 mm, linear to linear-lanceolate, usually with sterile shoots in the axils. Inflorescence a lax, (1)2- to 12-flowered panicle. Calyx (8-)11-20 mm, narrowly cylindrical, glandular-puberulent. Petals white or pale yellow; claw exserted, ciliate; coronal scales up to 1·5 mm. Capsule (3-)5-9 mm, ovoid, enclosed within the calyx, about as long as the pubescent carpophore. 2n = 24, 48. {\i S.E. Europe, southwards to} 40°{\i  N.} Bu Gr Ju Rm Rs(C, W, K, E) Tu.
