\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 91. S. cretacea} Fischer ex Sprengel,{\i  Syst. Veg.} ed. 16, {\b 2:} 405 (1825). Stems up to 30 cm, much-branched, with hoary pubescence below. Leaves up to 10 mm, linear, thick and rigid, acuminate. Inflorescence 1- to 3-flowered; pedicels usually shorter than calyx. Calyx 18-20 mm, glabrous or slightly scabrid on veins. Petals white; claw exserted; coronal scales absent. Capsule 10- 12 mm; carpophore 5-7 mm, stout. Seeds with flat faces and grooved back.{\i  Chalk hills. • S. Russia, E. Ukraine.} Rs(C, W, E).
