\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 94. S. linifolia} Sm. in Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1:} 301 (1809). Stems up to 65 cm, numerous, suberect, with short, hoary pubescence below, glabrous and viscid above. Basal leaves linear-lanceolate, puberulent. Inflorescence with few- or 1-flowered alternate branches; pedicels shorter than calyx. Calyx 15-20 mm, abruptly contracted below capsule, usually pubescent; teeth acute. Petals pinkish above, purplish beneath; claw ciliate; coronal scales truncate. Capsule 7-10 mm, equalling or somewhat longer than carpophore. 2n = 24. • {\i C. Greece.} Gr.
