\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 95. S. schwarzenbergeri} Halácsy, {\i Denkschr. Akad. Wiss. Math. Nat. Kl.} ({\i Wien}){\b  61:} 472 (1894) (incl. {\i S. horvatii} Micevski). Stems 10-45 cm, simple, erect from woody stock, slender, pubescent, viscid above. Basal leaves small, obovate-spathulate; upper cauline minute, linear. Inflorescence more or less racemose, 1- to 4-flowered; pedicels much shorter than calyx. Calyx 12-21 mm, puberulent; teeth ovate-lanceolate, more or less obtuse. Petals greenish; claw glabrous. Capsule equalling or somewhat shorter than carpophore. 2n = 24.{\i  Mountain rocks. • N.W. Greece and adjacent parts of Albania and Jugoslavia.} Al Gr Ju.
