\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b 97-102}).{\b  S. saxifraga} group. Caespitose perennials. Stems usually numerous, up to 20(-30) cm, suberect, slender, usually pubescent below, glabrous and viscid above. Leaves linear to linear-spathulate or linear-oblanceolate, often with scabrid or ciliate margins. Inflorescence 1- or 2(-4)-flowered. Calyx 6-16 mm, glabrous, pale, rarely vinous. Petals white above, reddish or greenish beneath; claw more or less exserted; coronal scales small. Capsule 5·5-12·5 mm; carpophore 2·5-12 mm, glabrous or slightly pubescent.
